                        <p>“We played against a very good team and learned about the physicality that comes in these big-time games,” senior Grayson Allen said. “We learned a lot about what we need to do better, and we can learn a lot from watching film from the second half. When we’re in such close games like that and we have Coach leading our team, we can be a very good basketball team.”</p>
<p><em>Hank Tucker and Sameer Pandhare contributed reporting.</em></p>

